Subject: Re: [T2] What's Involved: Converting 1.7/1.8 liter to 2.0 liter

At 03:14 PM 10/5/2002, RD Robertson wrote:
>Maybe someone out there who has rebuilt a 1.7 or 1.8 liter as a 2.0 liter
>engine can answer these questions: Does the crankcase have to be machined to
>accept larger cylinders?

No, up to 96mm will simply slip in.

> Replace the crankshaft with one that has a longer
>stroke?

Yes.


>How about hydraulic lifters? Is a hydraulic camshaft needed? Or just hydraulic
>lifters?

The debate is in the archives, you'll have to judge for yourself.

>Valve sizes?

Different, 2-liter heads have smaller valves.  Not a big deal.

>Anything else?

Yes, but nothing major.  Just use 2-liter crank and rods, and 94mm pistons/cylinders.  The valvetrain is an independent decision.

-David
